        caption: 'CRC-aided SC-List (CA-SCL) decoding. SCL explores the bit-decision tree breadth-first: at each information bit every surviving path branches into a 0 and a 1 continuation, and whenever the number of paths exceeds the list size L the decoder prunes back to the L paths of smallest path metric PM (a path is penalised by roughly |L_i| whenever its chosen bit fights the sign of its LLR). At the end L complete candidates remain (here L = 4). Plain SCL would output candidate A, which has the lowest metric (2.1) - but A fails the appended CRC. CA-SCL instead outputs B, the best-metric candidate that passes the CRC: the CRC acts as a path selector, not merely an error detector, rescuing the true codeword even when it is not metric-best. This polar + CRC + list scheme is what 5G NR uses on its control channels.'
